---
alwaysApply: true
---

- ALWAYS verify the existence of a file before referencing it or suggesting imports.
- STACK: React (Vite), Tailwind CSS, Supabase (v2), and LiteAPI. Do not suggest other libraries (like Axios) unless I explicitly ask; use standard 'fetch'.
- LITEAPI: Only use endpoints from 'https://api.liteapi.travel/v1/'. If unsure of a schema, ask me to provide the LiteAPI documentation snippet.
- DATABASE: We use a Supabase PostgreSQL schema. Always check the @supabase-db MCP for the latest table definitions before writing insert/update logic.
- ERROR HANDLING: Every database transaction must be wrapped in a try/catch block that specifically handles Postgres 'Exclusion Constraint' errors (code 23P01) for overlapping bookings.
- TYPESCRIPT: Use strict typing. Do not use 'any'. Use the 'Database' types generated by the Supabase CLI if available.
- UI: Use Tailwind utility classes only. Do not create separate CSS files.
